   "source": [
    "# Intro to SymPy \n",
    "\n",
    "Here we give a (quick) introduction to SymPy. This tutorial assumes you are already familiar with SymPy expressions, so this notebook should serve as a refresher."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "## Expressions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The function `init_printing()` will enable LaTeX pretty printing in the notebook for SymPy expressions. We recommend calling it at the top of any notebook that uses SymPy."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sympy import *\n",
    "init_printing()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "SymPy symbols are created with the `symbols()` function. SymPy expressions are built up from symbols, numbers, and SymPy functions, "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x, y, z = symbols('x y z')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "SymPy automatically pretty prints symbols with greek letters and subscripts."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "alpha1, omega_2 = symbols('alpha1 omega_2')\n",
    "alpha1, omega_2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sin(x + 1) - cos(y)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "### Exercise"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "Write a symbolic expression for $$\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2\\pi\\sigma^2} } \\; e^{ -\\frac{(x-\\mu)^2}{2\\sigma^2} }.$$ Remember that the function for $e^x$ is `exp(x)`. You will need to create symbols for `sigma` and `mu`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Write your answer here\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "## Some reminders on common gotchas:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "Dividing two integers in Python creates a float, like `1/2` -> `0.5`. If you want a rational number, use `Rational(1, 2)` or `S(1)/2`. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x + 1/2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x + S(1)/2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "`^` is the XOR operator. Use `**` for powers. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x ^ y"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x ** y"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "All SymPy expressions are immutable. Functions that operate on an expression return a new expression."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "expr = x + 1\n",
    "expr"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "expr.subs(x, 2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "expr"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "## Floating point representation\n",
    "\n",
    "Since most languages targeted will not support symbolic representation it is useful to let SymPy evaluate a floating point approximation (up to a user specified number of digits)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sqrt(2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sqrt(2).evalf(7)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "### Exercise\n",
    "Compute 100 digits of $\\pi$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Write your answer here\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "## Undefined functions\n",
    "\n",
    "Undefined functions are created with `Function()`. Undefined are useful to state that one variable depends on another (for the purposes of differentiation)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "f = Function('f')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "f(x) + 1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "## Derivatives\n",
    "\n",
    "Derivatives are computed with the `diff()` function, using the syntax `diff(expr, var1, var2, ...)`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "diff(sin(x + 1)*cos(y), x, y)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "diff(f(x) + 1, x)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "### Exercise"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "Write an expression representing the wave equation in one dimension: $${\\partial^2 u\\over \\partial t^2 } = c^2 { \\partial^2 u\\over \\partial  x^2}.$$ Remember that $u$ is a function in two variables. You can represent an equation using `Eq`, like"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Eq(x, y)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Write your answer here\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "## Matrices\n",
    "Matrices are created with `Matrix`. A matrix can contain any symbolic expression. See `Matrix?` for different ways to create a Matrix."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Matrix([[1, 2], [3, 4]])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# An unnested list will create a column vector\n",
    "Matrix([1, 2, 3])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Matrix([x, y, z])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "Matrices support all common operations, and have many methods for performing operations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Matrix([[1, 2], [3, 4]])*Matrix([x, y])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "for example, calculating the Jacobian matrix is as easy as:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Matrix([sin(x) + y, cos(y) + x, z]).jacobian([x, y, z])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "and for those of you who don't remember, the Jacobian is defined as:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "J = \\begin{bmatrix}\n",
    "\\frac{\\partial f_1}{\\partial x_1} &  \\frac{\\partial f_1}{\\partial x_2} & \\cdots \\\\\n",
    "\\frac{\\partial f_2}{\\partial x_1} &  \\frac{\\partial f_2}{\\partial x_2} & ~ \\\\\n",
    "\\vdots                            &  ~ & \\ddots \\\\\n",
    "\\end{bmatrix}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
       "you will come across this mathematical entity in later notebooks in this tutorial."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "### Exercise"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "Create the following matrix $$\\left[\\begin{matrix}1 & 0 & 1\\\\-1 & 2 & 3\\\\1 & 2 & 3\\end{matrix}\\right]$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Write your answer here\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
       "Now create a matrix representing $$\\left[\\begin{matrix}x\\\\y\\\\z\\end{matrix}\\right]$$ and multiply it with the previous matrix to get $$\\left[\\begin{matrix}x + z\\\\- x + 2 y + 3 z\\\\x + 2 y + 3 z\\end{matrix}\\right].$$\n",
       "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Write your answer here\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "Now take the Jacobian of that matrix with respect to your column vector, to get the original matrix back."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Write your answer here\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "## Matrix symbols\n",
    "\n",
    "SymPy can also operate on matrices of symbolic dimension ($n \\times m$). `MatrixSymbol(\"M\", n, m)` creates a matrix $M$ of shape $n \\times m$. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "n, m = symbols('n m', integer=True)\n",
    "M = MatrixSymbol(\"M\", n, m)\n",
    "b = MatrixSymbol(\"b\", m, 1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "M*b"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "(M*b).shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "Some matrix expression functions do not evaluate unless you call `doit`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Transpose(M*b)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Transpose(M*b).doit()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "### Exercise"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "Write a matrix expression representing $$Au + Bv,$$ where $A$ and $B$ are $100\\times 100$ and $u$ and $v$ are $100 \\times 1$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Write your answer here\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "## Indexed\n",
    "Indexed symbols can be created with `IndexedBase` and `Idx`. `IndexedBase(\"A\")` represents an array `A` and `Idx('i')` represents an index `i`. You can also use `symbols('i')` instead of `Idx('i')`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "A = IndexedBase(\"A\")\n",
    "i = Idx('i')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "A[i]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "### Exercise"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "Write an Indexed expression for $$A[i, j, k]$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Write your answer here\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "## Solving systems of equations\n",
    "\n",
    "A useful tool in your toolbelt when manipulating expressions is the ``solve`` function. `solve` solves equations symbolically (not numerically). The return value is a list of solutions.\n",
    "\n",
    "You can give `solve` an `Eq`, or if you give it an expression, it automatically assumes that it is equal to 0."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "solve(Eq(x**2, 4), x)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "solve(x**2 + 3*x - 3, x)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "It can also handle systems of equations. The return is a list of dictionaries, mapping symbols to solutions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "eq1 = x**2 + y**2 - 4  # circle of radius 2\n",
    "eq2 = 2*x + y - 1  # straight line: y(x) = -2*x + 1\n",
    "solve([eq1, eq2], [x, y])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "### Exercises "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "Solve the following system of equations: $$\\begin{align}z &= x^2 - y^2\\\\z^2 &= x^2 + y^2 + 4\\\\z &= x + y\\end{align}$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Write your answer here\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "source": [
    "## Solving differential equations\n",
    "If you are dealing with a differential equation, say:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "f''(x) = -f(x)\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "SymPy's dsolve can (sometimes) produce an exact symbolic solution. Like `solve`, `dsolve` assumes that expressions are equal to 0. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "deletable": true,
    "editable": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "f = Function('f')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
